          "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Production Deploy Script\n\n## Context\nNeed a one-command deploy script (`deploy.sh`) that provisions a fresh VPS with the streaming platform. The script should have polished terminal UX with spinners, step progress, and colors вҖ” like professional CLI tools.\n\n## What the script does\n\n```\n./deploy.sh\n  вҶ’ Prompts: IP, login, password\n  вҶ’ [1/7] Testing SSH connection\n  вҶ’ [2/7] Installing Docker on remote server\n  вҶ’ [3/7] Building Docker images (linux/amd64)\n  вҶ’ [4/7] Transferring images to server\n  вҶ’ [5/7] Generating config\n  вҶ’ [6/7] Deploying containers\n  вҶ’ [7/7] Verifying deployment\n  вҶ’ вң“ Done! Stream at http://<IP>\n```\n\n## Files to create\n\n### 1. `deploy.sh` вҖ” Main deploy script (~300 lines)\n\n**Terminal UX functions:**\n- `spinner()` вҖ” animated spinner (в Ӣв ҷв №в ёв јв ҙв Ұв §в Үв Ҹ) runs in background, killed on step completion\n- `step()` вҖ” prints `[1/7] в Ӣ Installing Docker...` with spinner, then `[1/7] вң“ Installing Docker` on success or `[1/7] вң— Installing Docker` + error on failure\n- Colors: green вң“, red вң—, cyan step text, bold headers\n- `banner()` вҖ” ASCII art header at start\n- `fatal()` вҖ” prints error in red, cleans up, exits 1\n\n**Flow:**\n\n1. **Prompt** вҖ” read IP, login, password (password hidden with `read -s`)\n2. **Test SSH** вҖ” `sshpass -p $PASS ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no $USER@$IP echo ok`\n3. **Install Docker** вҖ” runs remote script: install docker via official script, add user to docker group, start dockerd\n4. **Build images** вҖ” `docker build --platform linux/amd64 -t desent-server .` and `docker build --platform linux/amd64 -t desent-web ./web/liches-web` locally\n5. **Transfer images** вҖ” `docker save | ssh docker load` (with pv progress if available, plain pipe if not)\n6. **Generate config** вҖ” creates `docker-compose.prod.yml` on remote with auto-generated JWT_SECRET (openssl rand -hex 32), ships it via scp. Also creates Traefik config.\n7. **Deploy** вҖ” `ssh docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d`\n8. **Verify** вҖ” poll `http://$IP/health` until 200 or timeout\n\n**Requires locally:** `docker`, `sshpass` (script checks and tells user how to install if missing)\n\n### 2. `docker-compose.prod.yml` вҖ” Generated on the remote server\n\n```yaml\nservices:\n  traefik:\n    image: traefik:v3.3\n    command:\n      - --api.insecure=true\n      - --providers.docker=true\n      - --providers.docker.exposedbydefault=false\n      - --entrypoints.web.address=:80\n    ports:\n      - \"80:80\"\n      - \"8080:8080\"  # Traefik dashboard (optional, can remove)\n    volumes:\n      - /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock:ro\n    restart: unless-stopped\n\n  server:\n    image: desent-server:latest\n    labels:\n      - traefik.enable=true\n      - traefik.http.routers.api.rule=PathPrefix(`/api`) || PathPrefix(`/ws`) || PathPrefix(`/live`)\n      - traefik.http.routers.api.entrypoints=web\n      - traefik.http.services.api.loadbalancer.server.port=8080\n    ports:\n      - \"1935:1935\"  # RTMP вҖ” direct, not through Traefik\n    environment:\n      - JWT_SECRET=${JWT_SECRET}\n      - STREAM_KEY=live\n      - DB_PATH=/data/desent.db\n      - HLS_DIR=/tmp/hls\n      - HTTP_ADDR=:8080\n      - RTMP_ADDR=0.0.0.0:1935\n    volumes:\n      - db-data:/data\n    restart: unless-stopped\n\n  web:\n    image: desent-web:latest\n    labels:\n      - traefik.enable=true\n      - traefik.http.routers.web.rule=PathPrefix(`/`)\n      - traefik.http.routers.web.entrypoints=web\n      - traefik.http.routers.web.priority=1\n      - traefik.http.services.web.loadbalancer.server.port=3000\n    environment:\n      - NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=http://${SERVER_IP}\n    depends_on:\n      - server\n    restart: unless-stopped\n\nvolumes:\n  db-data:\n```\n\n**Routing via Traefik:**\n- `/api/*`, `/ws/*`, `/live/*` вҶ’ Go server (:8080) вҖ” higher priority (PathPrefix match)\n- `/*` (everything else) вҶ’ Next.js web (:3000) вҖ” priority=1 (lowest, catch-all)\n- `:1935` (RTMP) вҶ’ Go server directly (TCP, not HTTP, bypasses Traefik)\n- Traefik dashboard on :8080 (optional, for debugging)\n\n**Note on `NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL`:** The Next.js app uses this at build time for SSR and at runtime for client-side API calls. Since we're behind Traefik on the same origin, we set it to `http://<SERVER_IP>` so the browser hits Traefik which routes `/api/*` to the Go server.\n\n## Key decisions\n- **sshpass** for SSH auth (password-based, simplest for first-time VPS setup)\n- **docker save/load** to transfer images (no registry needed)\n- **Auto-generated JWT_SECRET** via `openssl rand -hex 32`\n- **Traefik v3** as reverse proxy (label-based routing, zero config files)\n- **No HTTPS/domain for now** вҖ” HTTP only on port 80, domain+TLS can be added later by updating Traefik config\n\n## Verification\n```bash\n# Test locally (dry run вҖ” just check prompts and validation)\nbash deploy.sh\n\n# Full test with a VPS\nbash deploy.sh\n# Enter IP, login, password\n# Watch each step complete\n# Open http://<IP> in browser вҖ” should see the web app\n# Stream with OBS to rtmp://<IP>:1935/live/live\n# Watch the stream on http://<IP>\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/m.ovchinnikov/.claude/projects/-Users-m-ovchinnikov-GolandProjects-twitch-desent/de384d35-0818-4fd9-9d1b-ca88dfe36a02.jsonl",
