          "text": "     1вҶ’# desent\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’Decentralized streaming platform where streamers self-host their own servers.\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’Each streamer runs a single Go binary that handles RTMP ingest, HLS transcoding, WebSocket chat, and user management with SQLite.\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’## Architecture\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’```\n    10вҶ’OBS (RTMP :1935) --> Go Server --> FFmpeg transcoder --> HLS segments\n    11вҶ’                        |\n    12вҶ’                        +--> HTTP :8080 (HLS delivery, REST API)\n    13вҶ’                        +--> WebSocket (chat)\n    14вҶ’                        +--> SQLite (users, sessions, bans)\n    15вҶ’```\n    16вҶ’\n    17вҶ’The server transcodes the incoming RTMP stream into multiple HLS quality levels (1080p, 720p, 480p, 360p) and serves them over HTTP. A WebSocket chat hub broadcasts messages to connected viewers.\n    18вҶ’\n    19вҶ’## Quick Start\n    20вҶ’\n    21вҶ’```bash\n    22вҶ’# 1. Clone\n    23вҶ’git clone https://github.com/yourname/desent.git && cd desent\n    24вҶ’\n    25вҶ’# 2. Set your JWT secret\n    26вҶ’export JWT_SECRET=\"your-secret-key\"\n    27вҶ’\n    28вҶ’# 3. Run with Docker Compose\n    29вҶ’docker compose up --build\n    30вҶ’```",
