          "text": "Here's my take on the open-source strategy:\n\n## What to open-source (the core streamer server)\n\n**Open-source the entire self-hosted streamer server.** This is your core value proposition вҖ” \"anyone can run their own streaming server.\" Open-sourcing it:\n\n- Builds trust (streamers can audit what they're running)\n- Gets community contributions (bug fixes, features, performance)\n- Drives adoption (the product IS the self-hosted server)\n\nSpecifically, these are safe and beneficial to open-source:\n\n| Component | Why |\n|-----------|-----|\n| `internal/ingest/` | RTMP + FFmpeg pipeline вҖ” generic, no competitive moat |\n| `internal/hls/` | HLS serving + caching вҖ” standard streaming tech |\n| `internal/chat/` | WebSocket chat + hub вҖ” well-known pattern |\n| `internal/auth/` | JWT auth вҖ” completely standard |\n| `internal/db/` | SQLite setup вҖ” no secrets here |\n| `internal/config/` | Env var config вҖ” trivial |\n| `internal/admin/` | Admin API вҖ” basic CRUD |\n| `web/` (frontend) | Player + admin panel вҖ” drives adoption |\n| `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml` | Deployment вҖ” essential for self-hosters |\n| `deploy.sh` | Deployment script вҖ” helps adoption |\n\n## What to keep closed-source (future components)\n\n| Component | Why |\n|-----------|-----|\n| **Bot detection / anti-abuse** | If attackers see the logic, they bypass it. View count fraud, chat spam bots, fake registrations вҖ” this is an arms race |\n| **Discovery Service** (moderation layer) | Your moderation algorithms, trust scoring, server ranking вҖ” this is your managed-service moat |\n| **Content moderation system** | Same вҖ” detection models, heuristics, blocklists |\n| **Installer / managed hosting orchestration** | The \"Amnezia-like\" UX that provisions VPS + domain + SSL automatically вҖ” this is your paid product differentiator |\n| **Analytics / monetization layer** | Viewer analytics, donation processing, subscription logic |\n| **Edge CDN coordination** | The protocol for origin вҶ” edge node sync, cache invalidation, load balancing logic |\n\n## Recommended structure\n\n```\ntwitch-desent/           вҶҗ Open source (MIT or AGPL)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ cmd/server/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ internal/            вҶҗ All current packages\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ web/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ Dockerfile\nв””в”Җв”Җ ...\n\ntwitch-desent-cloud/     вҶҗ Closed source (private repo)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ discovery/           вҶҗ Server catalog + moderation\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ antibot/             вҶҗ Bot detection, rate limiting heuristics\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ installer/           вҶҗ Managed deployment orchestration\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ edge/                вҶҗ CDN node coordination\nв””в”Җв”Җ moderation/          вҶҗ Content moderation pipeline\n```\n\n## The strategic logic\n\n**Open the commodity, close the moat.** The streaming server itself is commodity tech (FFmpeg + HLS + WebSocket). Your competitive advantages are:\n\n1. **Ease of deployment** (installer app) вҖ” closed\n2. **Network effects** (discovery catalog) вҖ” closed\n3. **Trust & safety** (moderation + anti-bot) вҖ” closed\n4. **Managed hosting** (the paid product) вҖ” closed\n\nThis is the same model as GitLab (open core), Supabase (open server, closed cloud features), and Bitwarden (open client, proprietary enterprise features).\n\nWant me to help set up the repo structure for this split, or draft a LICENSE file?",
