          "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Phase 6: Admin API вҖ” Implementation Plan\n\n## Context\n\nAdding admin-only REST API for managing server settings, users, and bans. All endpoints require JWT auth + admin role via existing `auth.RequireAuth` + `auth.RequireAdmin` middleware chain.\n\n## New Files\n\n```\ninternal/admin/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ handler.go   вҖ” admin REST endpoints (5 routes)\nв””в”Җв”Җ store.go     вҖ” settings + users + bans CRUD\n```\n\n## Modified Files\n\n- `internal/db/migrations.go` вҖ” add `bans` table\n- `cmd/server/main.go` вҖ” wire admin handler with auth middleware\n- `TODO.md` вҖ” mark Phase 5 done, Phase 6 done\n\n## Schema (add to migrations.go)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS bans (\n    id         INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n    user_id    INTEGER NOT NULL UNIQUE REFERENCES users(id),\n    reason     TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n    banned_by  INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),\n    created_at INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT (unixepoch())\n);\n```\n\n## Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | /api/admin/settings | Get all settings |\n| PUT | /api/admin/settings | Update settings (partial merge) |\n| GET | /api/admin/users | List all users with ban status |\n| POST | /api/admin/ban | Ban a user |\n| DELETE | /api/admin/ban/{userId} | Unban a user |\n\n## Design\n\n### store.go\n\nReuses `*db.DB` dual-pool pattern (Write for mutations, Read for queries).\n\nMethods:\n- `GetSettings(ctx) вҶ’ (map[string]string, error)` вҖ” SELECT all from settings table\n- `UpdateSettings(ctx, map[string]string) вҶ’ error` вҖ” UPSERT each key-value pair\n- `ListUsers(ctx) вҶ’ ([]UserInfo, error)` вҖ” LEFT JOIN users + bans\n- `BanUser(ctx, userID, bannedBy, reason) вҶ’ error` вҖ” INSERT into bans\n- `UnbanUser(ctx, userID) вҶ’ error` вҖ” DELETE from bans\n- `IsBanned(ctx, userID) вҶ’ (bool, error)` вҖ” for potential use in auth middleware later\n\n### handler.go\n\n- `RegisterRoutes(mux