          "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Admin Stats, Viewer Capacity & Quality Toggling\n\n## Context\n\nThe admin dashboard shows basic counts only. Qualities (720p/480p/360p at 30fps) are hardcoded throughout the backend. The streamer needs:\n\n1. **Server stats** вҖ” real system metrics (CPU%, system memory, uptime, HLS disk usage) on the admin dashboard\n2. **Viewer capacity** вҖ” how many concurrent viewers at each quality, based on configurable bandwidth\n3. **Quality toggling** вҖ” enable/disable qualities, persisted in DB, live FFmpeg restart\n4. **Expanded qualities** вҖ” add 4K 60fps, 1440p 60fps, 1080p 60fps, 720p 60fps alongside existing 480p/360p\n\nApproach: stdlib only for system stats (read `/proc/*` on Linux, `runtime` fallbacks on macOS). No GPU detection for now.\n\n## Quality Presets\n\n| Name | Resolution | FPS | Video kbps | Audio kbps | Total Mbps |\n|------|-----------|-----|-----------|-----------|-----------|\n| 2160p | 3840Г—2160 | 60 | 20000 | 192 | ~20.2 |\n| 1440p | 2560Г—1440 | 60 | 12000 | 160 | ~12.2 |\n| 1080p | 1920Г—1080 | 60 | 6000 | 128 | ~6.1 |\n| 720p | 1280Г—720 | 60 | 4000 | 128 | ~4.1 |\n| 480p | 854Г—480 | 30 | 1500 | 96 | ~1.6 |\n| 360p | 640Г—360 | 30 | 600 | 64 | ~0.7 |\n\nFFmpeg per-variant settings: 60fps variants use `-g:v:N 120 -keyint_min:v:N 120`, 30fps use `-g:v:N 60 -keyint_min:v:N 60`. Filter includes fps: `-filter:v:N \"scale=W:H,fps=FPS\"`.\n\nDefault enabled: 1080p, 720p, 480p, 360p (4K and 1440p disabled by default вҖ” most servers can't handle them).\n\n## Files Overview\n\n### New (2)\n```\ninternal/ingest/quality.go     вҖ” Quality type, AllQualities, helpers\ninternal/admin/sysinfo.go      вҖ” CPU%, system memory via /proc/* with runtime fallbacks\n```\n\n### Modified вҖ” Backend (6)\n```\ninternal/config/config.go      вҖ” add ServerBandwidthMbps\ninternal/ingest/ffmpeg.go      вҖ” dynamic buildFFmpegArgs with []Quality\ninternal/ingest/manager.go     вҖ” add SetQualities, EnabledQualities, Restart, StartedAt\ninternal/admin/handler.go      вҖ” add IngestManager interface, stats + quality endpoints\ninternal/hls/handler.go        вҖ” StreamStatusHandler reads dynamic qualities\ninternal/hls/cleaner.go        вҖ” scan subdirs dynamically\ncmd/server/main.go             вҖ” wire new deps, load persisted qualities\n```\n\n### Modified вҖ” Frontend (4)\n```\napps/web/lib/api-types.ts      вҖ” add ServerStats, QualitiesConfig types\napps/web/lib/api-client.ts     вҖ” add getAdminStats, getAdminQualities, updateAdminQualities\napps/web/app/admin/page.tsx    вҖ” stats bento cards + viewer capacity\napps/web/app/admin/settings/page.tsx вҖ” quality toggle switches section\n```\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### Step 1: `internal/ingest/quality.go` (new)\n\n```go\ntype Quality struct {\n    Name          string\n    Width         int\n    Height        int\n    FPS           int\n    VideoBitrateK int\n    MaxRateK      int\n    BufSizeK      int\n    AudioBitrateK int\n}\n```\n\n- `AllQualities` вҖ” ordered slice of all 6 presets (2160pвҶ’360p)\n- `DefaultQualities` вҖ” names enabled by default: `[\"1080p\",\"720p\",\"480p\",\"360p\"]`\n- `TotalBitrateMbps() float64` method\n- `QualityByName(name) *Quality`\n- `FilterQualities(enabled []string) []Quality`\n\n### Step 2: `internal/ingest/ffmpeg.go`\n\nChange `buildFFmpegArgs(rtmpURL, hlsDir string, qualities []Quality) []string`.\n\nKey changes for multi-FPS support:\n- Per-variant `-filter:v:N \"scale=W:H,fps=FPS\"` (embeds fps in filter chain)\n- Per-variant `-g:v:N GOP -keyint_min:v:N GOP` where GOP = FPS Г— 2\n- Remove the shared `-g 48 -keyint_min 48 -sc_threshold 0` вҖ” move to per-variant\n- Keep shared: `-c:v libx264 -preset veryfast -sc_threshold 0`\n- Dynamic `-var_stream_map` from quality names\n\n### Step 3: `internal/ingest/manager.go`\n\nAdd to `Manager`:\n- `qualities []Quality` field (default: `FilterQualities(DefaultQualities)`)\n- `startedAt time.Time`\n\nNew methods:\n- `SetQualities(names []string)` вҖ” mutex, never allows empty\n- `EnabledQualities() []string` вҖ” returns quality names\n- `Restart()` вҖ” SIGTERM to current FFmpeg, Run() loop auto-restarts\n- `StartedAt() time.Time`\n\nModify `runFFmpeg()`: snapshot `m.qualities` under lock, pass to `buildFFmpegArgs`.\n\n### Step 4: `internal/admin/sysinfo.go` (new)\n\nSystem stats collector, stdlib only:\n\n```go\ntype SysInfo struct {\n    CPUUsagePercent float64 // 0-100\n    CPUCores        int\n    MemTotalMB      float64\n    MemUsedMB       float64\n    MemUsedPercent  float64\n}\n\nfunc GetSysInfo() SysInfo\n```\n\nLinux (`/proc`):\n- CPU: read `/proc/stat` twice with 200ms gap, compute delta of idle vs total\n- Memory: parse `/proc/meminfo` for MemTotal, MemAvailable\n\nNon-Linux fallback:\n- CPU: `runtime.NumCPU()`, usage = 0 (not available)\n- Memory: `runtime.MemStats` Sys as approximation\n\nUse build tags: `sysinfo_linux.go` + `sysinfo_other.go`, or just `runtime.GOOS` check in a single file (simpler).\n\n### Step 5: `internal/config/config.go`\n\nAdd `ServerBandwidthMbps int`, env `SERVER_BANDWIDTH_MBPS`, default 100.\n\n### Step 6: `internal/admin/handler.go`\n\nAdd `IngestManager` interface:\n```go\ntype IngestManager interface {\n    IsLive() bool\n    EnabledQualities() []string\n    SetQualities(names []string)\n    Restart()\n    StartedAt() time.Time\n}\n```\n\nExpand `Handler` struct: add `ingestMgr IngestManager`, `hlsDir string`, `defaultBW int`.\nChange `NewHandler(store, ingestMgr, hlsDir, defaultBW)`.\n\nNew routes: `GET /api/admin/stats`, `GET /api/admin/qualities`, `PUT /api/admin/qualities`.\n\n**Stats endpoint** returns:\n```json\n{\n  \"uptime_seconds\": 86400,\n  \"cpu_usage_percent\": 23.5,\n  \"cpu_cores\": 4,\n  \"mem_total_mb\": 8192,\n  \"mem_used_mb\": 3500,\n  \"mem_used_percent\": 42.7,\n  \"mem_go_alloc_mb\": 12.5,\n  \"num_goroutines\": 15,\n  \"hls_disk_usage_mb\": 45.2,\n  \"stream_live\": true,\n  \"qualities\": [\"1080p\", \"720p\", \"480p\", \"360p\"],\n  \"bandwidth_mbps\": 100,\n  \"viewer_capacity\": {\"1080p\": 16, \"720p\": 24, \"480p\": 62, \"360p\": 150}\n}\n```\n\nBandwidth: check settings DB for `server_bandwidth_mbps`, fallback to env var default.\n\n**Quality endpoints**:\n- `GET /api/admin/qualities` вҶ’ `{ enabled: [...], available: [...] }`\n- `PUT /api/admin/qualities` вҶ’ validates names, persists as `qualities_enabled: \"720p,480p,360p\"` in settings, calls `SetQualities` + `Restart` if live, returns `{ enabled, available, restarted }`\n\n### Step 7: `internal/hls/handler.go` + `cleaner.go`\n\n`handler.go`: `StreamStatusHandler(lc LiveChecker, ql QualityLister)` вҖ” `ql.EnabledQualities()` replaces hardcoded list.\n\n`cleaner.go`: Replace `variants := []string{\"720p\",\"480p\",\"360p\"}` with `os.ReadDir(hlsDir)` to iterate subdirectories.\n\n### Step 8: `cmd/server/main.go`\n\n- Load `qualities_enabled` from settings DB before creating ingest manager\n- `ingestMgr.SetQualities(parsed)` before `Run()`\n- Create HLS dirs for ALL qualities (all 6)\n- `admin.NewHandler(adminStore, ingestMgr, cfg.HLSDir, cfg.ServerBandwidthMbps)`\n- `hlsHandler.StreamStatusHandler(ingestMgr, ingestMgr)`\n\n### Step 9: Frontend types + API client\n\n**`api-types.ts`** вҖ” add:\n```ts\nexport type ServerStats = {\n  uptime_seconds: number\n  cpu_usage_percent: number\n  cpu_cores: number\n  mem_total_mb: number\n  mem_used_mb: number\n  mem_used_percent: number\n  mem_go_alloc_mb: number\n  num_goroutines: number\n  hls_disk_usage_mb: number\n  stream_live: boolean\n  qualities: string[]\n  bandwidth_mbps: number\n  viewer_capacity: Record<string, number>\n}\n\nexport type QualitiesConfig = {\n  enabled: string[]\n  available: string[]\n  restarted?: boolean\n}\n```\n\n**`api-client.ts`** вҖ” add: `getAdminStats()`, `getAdminQualities()`, `updateAdminQualities(enabled[])`.\n\n### Step 10: Admin dashboard (`app/admin/page.tsx`)\n\nAdd `api.getAdminStats()` to the parallel fetch. New bento card rows:\n\n**System stats row** (4 cards):\n- **cpu** вҖ” `X%` usage + core count subtitle\n- **memory** вҖ” `X / Y MB` used/total + percent subtitle\n- **goroutines** вҖ” count\n- **HLS disk** вҖ” `X MB`\n\n**Viewer capacity section** (card with sub-grid):\n- Header: \"viewer capacity\" + bandwidth display\n- Grid of per-quality cards: quality name + max viewer count\n- Only shows enabled qualities\n\n### Step 11: Quality toggles (`app/admin/settings/page.tsx`)\n\nNew \"stream qualities\" section above the generic key-value settings:\n- Bento card per available quality (2-col grid)\n- Each card: quality name, resolution + fps + bitrate info\n- Toggle switch (accent color when on)\n- Last enabled toggle disabled (can't have zero)\n- On toggle: calls `updateAdminQualities`, toast with restart warning if live\n- Visual grouping: 60fps qualities vs 30fps qualities\n\n## Quality Toggle Data Flow\n\n```\nAdmin toggles 480p OFF вҶ’\n  PUT /api/admin/qualities { enabled: [\"1080p\",\"720p\",\"360p\"] } вҶ’\n  validate вҶ’ persist \"qualities_enabled\" to SQLite вҶ’\n  ingestMgr.SetQualities вҶ’ ingestMgr.Restart (if live) вҶ’\n  Run() loop вҶ’ runFFmpeg() with new quality list вҶ’\n  response { enabled, available, restarted: true } вҶ’\n  toast \"qualities updated, stream restarting\"\n```\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\ngo build ./cmd/server && go test ./...\ncd web/liches-web && pnpm build\n```\n\n1. `/admin` вҖ” see CPU%, memory, goroutines, disk cards\n2. Viewer capacity shows estimates for all enabled qualities\n3. `/admin/settings` вҖ” see 6 quality toggle cards (4 on by default, 2160p/1440p off)\n4. Toggle 480p off вҶ’ toast warns about restart вҶ’ stream status returns fewer qualities\n5. Try enabling 2160p вҶ’ works, capacity shows low viewer count (high bitrate)\n6. Can't disable last quality вҖ” toggle disabled\n7. Restart server вҖ” persisted qualities load correctly\n8. On Linux: CPU% and memory show real system stats\n9. On macOS: CPU% shows 0 (fallback), memory from Go runtime\n\n\nIf y