            "new_string": "## Conventions\n\n- Use Go stdlib where possible (`net/http`, `log/slog`, `encoding/json`)\n- Structured logging with `log/slog`\n- Errors: wrap with `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`\n- No frameworks вҖ” keep dependencies minimal\n- Tests alongside code (`*_test.go` in same package)\n- Context propagation through all handlers\n- Graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n\n## Codebase Patterns\n\n### Module Wiring\nEach package follows the pattern: `NewStore(db)` вҶ’ `NewHandler(store, deps)` вҶ’ `handler.RegisterRoutes(mux)`.\nAll wiring happens in `cmd/server/main.go`. No dependency injection framework вҖ” explicit construction.\n\n### Database Access\n- `db.DB` has `.Write` (1 conn) and `.Read` (4 conns) pools вҖ” use Write for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE, Read for SELECT\n- SQLite with WAL mode, foreign keys enabled, 5s busy timeout\n- Schema in `internal/db/migrations.go` as a single `const schema` string executed on startup\n- Timestamps stored as Unix epoch integers via `DEFAULT (unixepoch())`\n\n### Auth Flow\n- `auth.TokenService` generates/validates JWT tokens with `Claims{UserID, Username, Role}`\n- First registered user auto-promoted to admin role\n- WS auth: JWT passed as `?token=` query param (browser WS API can't set headers)\n- HTTP auth: JWT in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header, extracted by `auth.Middleware`\n\n### Chat Architecture\n- Hub pattern: single goroutine event loop (select on register/unregister/broadcast/ticker/ctx.Done)\n- Hub polls `ingest.Manager.IsLive()` every 2s to auto-create/close `stream_sessions`\n- Messages persisted only when stream is live (sessionID > 0)\n- Client has separate readPump (reads JSON from WS) and writePump (writes from send channel) goroutines\n- Rate limiting: per-client, configurable via `CHAT_RATE_LIMIT_MS` (default 500ms)\n- Message length cap: `CHAT_MAX_MSG_LEN` (default 500 chars, truncated silently)\n- JSON wire format: `{\"type\":\"chat\"|\"system\", \"text\":\"...\", \"user_id\":N, \"username\":\"...\", \"timestamp\":N}`\n\n### Config\nAll config via environment variables with sensible defaults. `getEnv(key, fallback)` and `getEnvInt(key, fallback)` helpers.\n\n### Ingest/Streaming\n- `ingest.Manager.Run(ctx)` вҖ” infinite loop: start FFmpeg with `-listen 1`, wait for exit, restart after 2s\n- `Manager.IsLive()` returns `running` field (protected by mutex), set true on FFmpeg start, false on exit\n- `LiveChecker` interface (defined in `hls` and `chat` packages) вҖ” `IsLive() bool`\n- HLS cleaner runs as background goroutine, removes old `.ts` segments",
